comment:
* This groups the BSF (BootStrapping Function) related configs.
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 24.109.

variables.name: KEY_BSF_SERVER_FQDN_STRING
variables.comment:
Specifies the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of BSF Server
         * as per 3GPP 24.109.

variables.name: KEY_BSF_SERVER_PORT_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the port number of the BSF server as per 3GPP 24.109.
         * This is usually default port number of HTTP, i.e. 80.

variables.name: KEY_BSF_TRANSPORT_TYPE_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the transport type used in communication with * BSF server. * *

Possible values are, * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TCP}, * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TLS} * *

If key is invalid or not configured, the default value * {@link Ims#PREFERRED_TRANSPORT_TCP} will apply.
